author: CNN
description: CNN’s Kasie Hunt asks Rep. Mike Lawler (R-NY) about the confrontation he had with Rep. Hakeem Jeffries (D-NY). #CNN #News
title: Rep Lawler on his confrontation with Hakeem Jeffries

author: CNN
description: Roads flooded the streets of Charleston, South Carolina on Friday from a major Atlantic storm system, with more major coastal flooding expected along the East Coast.
title: Major storm floods streets in Charleston

author: CNN
description: The 72-hour period for the release of the hostages held by Hamas has now begun, and nearly 2,000 Palestinian prisoners and detainees in Israel will also be freed as part of the agreement. US President Donald Trump will visit Israel on Monday, according to police. #CNN #News
title: Ceasefire: 47 hostages remain to be released within 72 hours

author: CNN
description:
The Trump administration has begun firing federal workers, the White House’s budget chief announced Friday, as Republicans look to maximize pressure on the Democratic Party more than a week into the government shutdown.

“The RIFs have begun,” Office of Management and Budget Director Russell Vought posted on X, announcing the the government-wide reductions in force that have been anticipated since federal funding lapsed on October 1. #CNN #News
title: Russell Vought: Federal layoffs have begun

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump made an unusual return to the medical center. CNN's Alayna Treene reports from the White House. #cnn #trump #exam #walterreedmedicalcenter
title: Trump goes to Walter Reed for second medical exam

author: CNN
description: First lady Melania Trump said Friday that Russia has allowed eight Ukrainian children to reunite with their parents, following months of private discussions between Russian officials and the first lady’s office centered on children separated from their families during the war.
title: Melania Trump describes working with Putin on family reunions

author: CNN
description: Ted Turner’s nature reserve, Vermejo, is the subject of a new documentary. “Preserved” highlights the 558,000-acre reserve where a once neglected ecosystem is thriving. #CNN #climate #vermejo #nature
title: Nature rebounds on Ted Turner’s reserve

author: CNN
description: Office of Management and Budget Director Russell Vought announced on Friday that the government has started firing federal workers during the government shutdown.
title: WH budget chief announces firing of federal workers has begun

author: CNN
description: Thousands of displaced Palestinians are returning to the north of Gaza as the ceasefire deal between Hamas and Israel takes effect. CNN’s Clarissa Ward reports from Tel Aviv, Israel, on what this new chapter could mean for both people in Gaza and Israel. #cnn #news
title: Thousands of displaced Palestinians return to north

author: CNN
description:
Several people are dead and other people are missing after an explosion at a military explosives company in Tennessee, local officials say.

#CNN #News #Explosion #Tennessee
title: Deadly explosion at explosives factory

author: CNN
description: Rescue teams in Tennessee are responding to an explosion at Accurate Energetic Systems, which specializes in making military explosives. CNN's Ryan Young reports. #CNN #News
title: Massive blast at military explosives plant in Tennessee leaves multiple people dead

author: CNN
description: Attorney General Pam Bondi was caught off guard Thursday when President Donald Trump’s handpicked US attorney, Lindsey Halligan, secured New York Attorney General Letitia James’ indictment from a grand jury, two sources familiar with what happened told CNN. CNN’s Kristen Holmes reports. #CNN #News
title: Pam Bondi caught off guard by Lindsey Halligan’s indictment of Letitia James

author: CNN
description: Members of the National Guard were absent Friday from outside an Immigration and Customs Enforcement facility in Broadview, Illinois, a day after a federal judge temporarily halted the Trump administration’s deployment of Guard troops in the state. CNN’s Whitney Wild reports.  #CNN #News
title: After judge’s ruling, National Guard troops absent outside Chicago area ICE facility

author: CNN
description: A Tampa bus driver is being praised for rescuing a young child wandering alone in traffic — stopping her route to bring him to safety until police arrived. #CNN #News
title: Tampa bus driver saves lost child

author: CNN
description: Eighty years after the Japanese surrendered, formally ending World War II, CNN’s Stephanie Elam sat down with US Navy veteran Edgar Buffman, who served on the USS Missouri during the war. Buffman says he was 18 when he first boarded the Missouri and was never afraid going to war because “you did what had to be done.” He recalls what life was like on the “Mighty Mo,” witnessing the aftermath of a kamikaze attack, and watching as members of the Japanese Imperial Government boarded the Missouri on September 2, 1945, to take part in the surrender ceremony. #CNN #News
title: WWII Navy vet explains what it was like to head towards Japan at 18 years old

author: CNN
description:
During a Trump administration Cabinet meeting, HHS Secretary Robert F. Kennedy Jr. claimed there was a link between autism and Tylenol use after babies are circumcised. Experts say there are multiple causes of autism, and the science showing a connection between autism and Tylenol is not settled.

#CNN #News #Health #Autism #Tylenol
title: RFK Jr. suggests link between autism and Tylenol use after circumcision

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Salma Abdelaziz (@saziz88) breaks down some of what we know after the Israeli government approves a Gaza ceasefire resolution. #CNN #news
title: The latest on the ceasefire deal

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Ivan Watson reports from Macao, where there’s a great deal of enthusiasm at the return of the NBA, with two pre-season games between the Phoenix Suns and the Brooklyn Nets this weekend. #CNN #News
title: NBA games back in China after six years

author: CNN
description: Longtime team chaplain for Loyola University Chicago, Sister Jean Dolores Schmidt, has died aged 106. Sister Jean shot to fame in 2018 after TV cameras caught her pre-game prayer for the Ramblers basketball team and her cheering from the sidelines during the NCAA tournament. #cnn #loyolauniversitychicago #sisterjean
title: Loyola Chicago’s beloved Sister Jean dies at 106

author: CNN
description: The leader of the democracy movement in Venezuela, María Corina Machado, has won the Nobel Peace Prize. In a phone call, the secretary of the Norwegian Nobel Committee informed Machado that she won. Machado is currently in hiding and wanted for crimes by the authoritarian Maduro regime. #cnn #news
title: Machado wins Nobel Peace Prize while in hiding

author: CNN
description: The Israeli military said Friday that a ceasefire was now in effect in Gaza, as its forces pull back in accordance with the deal approved by the government overnight. The Israel Defense Forces spokesperson added, however, that “troops will continue to be present in various areas of the Gaza Strip.” #CNN #News
title: Israel says Gaza ceasefire in place as troops pull back

author: CNN
description: María Corina Machado has been announced as the winner of the Nobel Peace Prize 2025 for “promoting democratic rights for the people of Venezuela.” She is Venezuela’s main opposition leader, who is in hiding. #CNN #News
title: María Corina Machado wins Nobel Peace Prize

author: CNN
description: Democrat Katie Porter’s campaign for California governor is going viral after a contentious interaction with the press and a video where she appeared to snap at a staffer who interrupted an interview. The CNN NewsNight panel debates whether the backlash she’s gotten is unfair given President Trump’s treatment of the press. #CNN #News
title: Double Standard? MAGA dunks on Katie Porter's viral videos

author: CNN
description:
To mark World Mental Health Day, the Prince of Wales sat down for a conversation with Rhian Mannings, whose husband took his life days after the sudden death of their son in 2012. William’s Royal Foundation is launching a new National Suicide Prevention Network in an effort to transform suicide prevention in the country. 
Editors note: Help is available if you or someone you know is struggling with suicidal thoughts or mental health matters. In the US: Call or text 988, the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline. Globally: The International Association for Suicide Prevention and Befrienders Worldwide have contact information for crisis centers around the world.
title: Prince William fights back tears as widow talks about husband’s suicide

author: CNN
description: North Korea has revived its Mass Games for the first time in five years, mobilizing an estimated 100,000 citizens in tightly choreographed displays honoring Kim Jong Un and the ruling party. Participation is mandatory and demands months of grueling rehearsals, as CNN’s Will Ripley reports. #CNN #News #NorthKorea
title: North Korea stages massive celebration for ruling party's 80th anniversary

author: CNN
description: María Corina Machado has been announced as the winner of the Nobel Peace Prize 2025 for “promoting democratic rights for the people of Venezuela.” She is Venezuela’s main opposition leader, who is in hiding. #cnn #mariacorinamachado #nobelpeaceprize
title: María Corina Machado wins Nobel Peace Prize

author: CNN
description:
Dr. Sanjay Gupta talks with oncologist Dr. Kimmie Ng about the surprising rise in cancer among young adults, why colorectal cancer is leading the trend, and the warning signs you shouldn’t ignore.

Listen to the full episode on CNN's Chasing Life podcast: https://swap.fm/l/clytb101025

#cnn #news #health #cancer #sanjaygupta #drsanjaygupta
title: Why are so many young people getting cancer? | Chasing Life

author: CNN
description: Cardinal Pierbattista Pizzaballa, the Latin Patriarch of Jerusalem who witnessed the catastrophe inside Gaza, speaks to CNN’s Erin Burnett about the ceasefire and the current situation on the ground. #cnn, #news, #politics
title: Latin Patriarch of Jerusalem speaks out on Gaza

author: CNN
description: The Trump administration plans to roll out a video at airports across the United States that will blame Democrats for lapses in Transportation Security Administration workers’ pay because of the government shutdown.
title: Video of Kristi Noem on shutdown blame to roll out airports

author: CNN
description: A federal judge has granted a temporary restraining order blocking President Donald Trump’s National Guard deployment in Illinois for two weeks. Texas guardsmen have been on the ground in the greater Chicago area, with the Trump administration saying they were needed to protect ICE and other federal property and personnel.
title: Judge grants temporary restraining order blocking troops in Illinois

author: CNN
description: An appeals court hearing on whether the Trump administration should be blocked from federalizing the Oregon National Guard to respond to ICE protests in Portland concluded. The hearing, originally scheduled for 40 minutes, lasted more than an hour as the three judges pressed both sides with questions about the law and the impact of the protests on federal agents.
title: Appeals court weighs Trump's deployment of troops to Portland

author: CNN
description:
A Texas court has again granted a stay of execution to death row inmate Robert Roberson, who has long claimed he is innocent in the murder of his 2-year-old daughter Nikki Curtis, saying his conviction based on a diagnosis of shaken baby syndrome was flawed.
The ruling Thursday by the Texas Court of Criminal Appeals halts Roberson’s execution scheduled to take place October 16, which his attorneys have said would be the first in the US based on an allegation of shaken baby syndrome. #CNN #News
title: Texas court halts execution of death row inmate who claims innocence

author: CNN
description:
New York Attorney General Letitia James was indicted Thursday in Alexandria, Virginia, as President Donald Trump’s Justice Department continues to pursue charges against his political opponents.

James has been under investigation since May over a 2023 mortgage she took out to buy a home in Norfolk, Virginia.

The grand jury returned two felony charges: bank fraud and making false statements to a financial institution. James’ first court appearance is scheduled for October 24 in Norfolk. #CNN #News
title: 'Baseless charges': NY Attorney General Letitia James responds to Trump in new video

author: CNN
description: New York Attorney General Letitia James posts a video in response to the Trump administration indicting her on two felony charges.
title: New York AG Letitia James responds to Trump in new video

author: CNN
description: CNN's Anderson Cooper speaks with an Israeli woman who had family members kidnapped on October 7 and later killed in Gaza  about how she feels about the ceasefire plan.
title: Family of deceased hostages on hope for the future
